Package org.ivoa.dm.stc.coords

Class SpaceFrame

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ivoa.dm.stc.coords.CoordFrame
      • org.ivoa.dm.stc.coords.SpaceFrame
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulations, org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulationsForObjectType<java.lang.Long>
    @Entity
@VoDml(id="coords:SpaceFrame",
       role=objectType)
public class SpaceFrame
extends CoordFrame
implements org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulationsForObjectType<java.lang.Long>
    A SpaceFrame is specified by its reference frame (orientation), and a reference position (origin). Currently only standard reference frames are allowed. An equinox MUST be provided for pre-ICRS reference frames. A planetary ephemeris MAY be provided if relevant. If needed, but not provided, it is assumed to be 'DE405'. objectType: SpaceFrame
